y of cities. Thus it provides critical wisdom\nneeded for urban healthcare policy and resource management. The pandemic\nvulnerability index calculation method and the process present a blueprint for\nthe development of similar indices for cities in other countries, leading to a\nbetter understanding and improved pandemic management for urban areas and\npost-pandemic urban planning across the world.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Mar 2022 17:00:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
